# ---- credentialed data: NEVER commit (PhysioNet DUA) ----
# Use data/* (not data/) so git can still descend to keep the README.
data/*
!data/README.md
*.parquet
*.csv.gz
*.hea
*.dat
*.wfdb

# ---- secrets: NEVER commit ----
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem
**/.mcp.json
secrets.*
*_api_key*
*credentials*

# ---- model weights: never ship (users pull MedGemma themselves) ----
*.safetensors
*.gguf
*.bin
models/

# ---- results: ship only curated public/aggregate outputs, never row-level PHI ----
results/private/
results/**/*_raw*.csv
# adjudication.html is a ~29MB generated artifact (base64-embedded PNGs); regenerates
# in ~0.3s via scripts/52_build_adjudication_app.py, so never commit it.
results/gallery/adjudication.html
# The blinded second-pass re-read staging directory is fully regenerated by
# scripts/60_stage_blinded_reread.py (568 PNG copies + reread.html). The hidden
# de-blinding key _blind_map.csv is the only de-anonymizing link and must not be
# pushed. The whole directory regenerates in ~0.3s, so never commit it.
results/gallery_readjud_blind/

# ---- archived null artifacts: keep on disk, never push ----
**/_archive_v1_null/

# ---- run-time logs (may contain absolute home paths in error traces) ----
logs/
*.log
!figures/figures_buildlog.md
!manuscript/**/buildlog.md

# ---- python / tooling ----
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
dist/
build/
*.egg-info/
.DS_Store

# ---- LaTeX build artifacts (the manuscript .tex is tracked; outputs are not) ----
*.aux
*.bbl
*.blg
*.fdb_latexmk
*.fls
*.lof
*.lot
*.out
*.synctex.gz
*.toc
manuscript/tex/*.log
manuscript/tex/*.pdf

# ---- IDE / editor cruft ----
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.d6_scratch/

# ============================================================================
# RELEASE BLOCK (2026-06-01) — public-bound file set
# The orchestrator finalized the public set; everything below is internal-only
# and must NOT ship. Rules here are intentionally placed last so they win over
# any earlier negation (e.g. the figures_buildlog.md re-include above).
# ============================================================================
# Entire results tree: row-level/aggregate outputs, galleries, weights, logs.
results/
# All internal evidence/build workbooks EXCEPT the prereg. Use findings/* (not
# findings/) so the negation below can re-include the single shipping file.
findings/*
!findings/preregistration_detector.md
# Immutable internal narrative record.
docs/
# Internal planning / handoff / decision artifacts at repo root.
/HANDOFF.md
/task_plan.md
/progress.md
/findings.md
# All HTML (covers decisions.html and release_submission_steps.html).
*.html
# Editor / pipeline backup files.
*.bak
# Figure card list and build log (not part of the public figure set).
figures/fig_disagreement_examples_cardlist.csv
figures/figures_buildlog.md
# Scratch determinism verifier (the shipped verifier lives elsewhere).
scripts/_verify_determinism.py

# ============================================================================
# RELEASE BLOCK ADDENDUM (2026-06-03) — design-exploration scratch
# Manuscript switched to Layout B; the A/B/C layout experiments, concept
# figures, concept scripts, and LaTeX page thumbnails are internal scratch and
# must NOT ship. The real pipeline (scripts/10-61), the manuscript source, and
# the figure PDFs/PNGs the manuscript uses are NOT covered here and still ship.
# ============================================================================
# A/B/C manuscript layout experiments (PDFs, _layout_plan / _integration_plan,
# layout_comparison.html). *.html is already ignored above; the dir catches the
# rest (per-layout .tex/.pdf/.aux and the planning markdown).
manuscript/layouts/
# Concept/exploratory figures + their gallery (PDF/PNG/thumbnails).
figures/concepts/
# Concept/exploratory figure scripts.
scripts/concepts/
# LaTeX page-thumbnail renders used only for layout QC.
manuscript/tex/thumb_*.png
# Other LaTeX build/QC scratch in the tex dir: full-page renders (page-NN.png),
# QA crops (qa-NN.png), the concatenated-log dump (full.txt), and layout-config
# snapshots (manuscript.tex.cfg*). Only manuscript.tex + the canonical bib ship.
manuscript/tex/page-*.png
manuscript/tex/qa-*.png
manuscript/tex/full.txt
manuscript/tex/manuscript.tex.cfg*

